org.apache.juneau.rest.exception

Class MethodNotAllowed

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • org.apache.juneau.rest.RestException
            • org.apache.juneau.rest.exception.MethodNotAllowed
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @Response(code=405,
          description="Method Not Allowed")
public class MethodNotAllowed
extends RestException
    Exception representing an HTTP 405 (Method Not Allowed).

    A request method is not supported for the requested resource; for example, a GET request on a form that requires data to be presented via POST, or a PUT request on a read-only resource.
